content.description: This is the left line up the slab boulder under the Stone Tower. Sit start on the furthest left side of a big jug rail using a big foot rail. One tricky move leads to a fun slab.
content.location: It is below Fist Fucker not the Stone Tower Boulder.

content.description:
Mantel It Out starts on a big jug in the middle of the rail/face of boulder. Sit start on a jug with good feet, mantel it out, and finish on Slabba Dabba Dooo. 

  This needs a bit more cleaning but is a fun warm-up.
content.location: This is the middle line, starting off a big jug in the middle with good feet below.

content.description:
This is the first right problem. It climbs better than it looks. 

  Sit start on the farthest right side of the jug rail, using good feet. Bump your right hand out using small crimp (if short) to a three finger dish. Bump the hand again up to a good hand, make a cool foot move, and top out. Walk off right. 

  This is probably harder than a V2 if you are short... that's why I gave it a 2+.
content.location: It is the furthest right route on the Dungeon Boulder below Stone Tower Boulder.

content.description:
This is the boulder that is directly below Fist Fucker on the Stone Tower Boulder.

3 slabby new problems exist here.

There are fun warm-ups and good boulders for beginner climbers!
